	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Membler's emulator is just an emulator - it would likely draw a lot of performance in a game </div>
<br />
<br />Not any more than it would on the NES. The music driver can be executed natively on the S-CPU as long as some RAM has been set aside for it. Then you'd have to send the updated APU register values to the S-SMP (i.e. 24 bytes per frame) and let it do the rest.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


